The paper discusses the use of time series models to analyze sequential data from a MOOC, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also draws an analogy to language modeling, which suggests that it could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for recommendation, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of digital learning environments, which could fall under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
